headline: Why Humana (HUM) Shares Are Plunging Today
summary: Shares of health insurance company Humana (NYSE:HUM) fell 5.2% in the afternoon session after the company announced it will reduce the reach of its Medicare Advantage plans next year, citing rising costs. The health insurer will decrease its Medicare Advantage presence from 48 states to 46 and will cover 85% of U.S. counties, down from 89% this year.
